radiographic_examinations.findings: Bibasilar atelectasis. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. The appendix is dilated at its mid to distal portion to 12 mm, with mild surrounding fat stranding. Trace free fluid in the pelvis. No evidence of focal lesions in liver, pancreas, spleen, kidneys, or gallbladder. No retroperitoneal or mesenteric lymphadenopathy. Mild atherosclerotic disease noted. An umbilical hernia containing fat is present.
